{"questionId":"1250688","questionHtml":"<p>Wavefronts travel from air to medium Q as shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e5d5bf404e0b0f373a22930a852ada9023c8efae.png\" width=\"368\" height=\"162\"></p>\n<p>What is the refractive index of Q?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1250688","referenceCode":"20N.1A.SL.TZ0.12","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Wavefronts travel from air to medium Q as shown. What is the refractive index of Q? A. sin30°sin45° B. sin45°sin30° C. sin45°sin60° D. sin60°sin45°","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"12","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["C. Wave behaviour","C.3 Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}